<- Vector ----------------------------------------------------------------------
This class represent direction. This class wait an array with this key :
	-> 'dest' : Vertex from the Vertex class of the vector destination
	-> 'orig' : Original vertex

It contains these methods :
	=> float magnitude() : return the length of vector
	=> Vector normalize() : return the normalize vector. If already normalize
return a fresh copy of it.
	=> Vector add( Vector $rhs ) : return the sum of two vectors
	=> Vector sub( Vector $rhs ) : return the difference of two vectors
	=> Vector opposite() : return opposite vector
	=> Vector scalarProduct( $k) : return the vector with scalar
	=> float dotProduct( Vector $rhs) : return the product Scalar of two vectors
	=> float cos( vector $rhs ) : return cosine of the angle
	=> Vector crossProduct( vector $rhs ) : return the cross product of two vectors
	(right hand reference)
---------------------------------------------------------------------- Vector ->
